WAIT       DOS Version           May 28 1991

USAGE:     WAIT [-?#fhkqux] [message]

WHERE:     -?  This help.
           -#  Delay to timeout in seconds, default is 60.
           -f  Wait forever for key, no timeout.
           -h  This help.
           -k  Ignore Keyboard, always timeout.
           -n  no processing of \a \b \f \n \r \t \v \x00 in msg.
           -q  quiet mode. do not display msg.
           -u  convert char read to uppercase.
           -x  strip high bit from message params.

This program waits for a key and returns its ascii value.

